snippet.title: Wham! - Last Christmas (Japanese Lyrics)
snippet.description:
ワム！ - ラスト・クリスマス | Wham! - Last Christmas
Stream and download: https://wham.lnk.to/40LastChristmas
More here: https://Wham.lnk.to/Playlists
Subscribe to the Wham! YouTube Channel: https://Wham.lnk.to/YT_Subscribe  
🎧ストリーミング再生： https://WhamJP.lnk.to/LastChristmas　

【楽曲情報】
イギリスのポップ・デュオ＝ワム！（Wham!）が1984年12月にリリースしたクリスマス・ソングの金字塔「ラスト・クリスマス」。
「去年のクリスマス　君に僕の心を捧げたのに / すぐ翌日に君はそれを放り出してしまった　/　今年はもう涙はごめんだから / 誰か他の特別な人にあげることにするよ」
恋人に裏切られたクリスマスの悲しみを綴った切ない歌詞と、軽快でポップなサウンドが相まって、世界中で＜クリスマスの大定番曲＞として今なお色褪せない輝きを放ちつづける名曲です。

------------------------------------------------------
去年のクリスマス　君に僕の心を捧げたのに
すぐ翌日に君はそれを放り出してしまった
今年はもう涙はごめんだから
誰か他の特別な人にあげることにするよ

一度の失敗にすっかり尻ごみして
ずっと距離をおいているのに　君はいまだに僕の目をとらえて離さない
教えておくれ、ベイビー　僕のこと覚えてる？
そうさ、あれから1年　忘れてたって別に驚きもしないよ
（ハッピー・クリスマス）
リボンをかけて送り届けた
「愛してる」ってメッセージをつけて　あれは本気だったんだ
今になって自分がどんなに馬鹿だったかわかったよ
でも、もし今、君がキスしてくれたら　きっとまた僕は騙されてしまうんだろうな

混雑した部屋　疲れた目をした友人たち
僕は隠れてるんだ　君と、その氷のような心から
何てことだろう　君を信頼できる人だと思ってたなんて
僕？　僕はただ単に都合のいい相談相手だったんだね
心に炎を燃やした恋人の顔
ひっそり君を想っていた　なのに君は僕を引き裂いた
だけど今、僕は本当の愛を見つけた　もう二度と君に惑わされはしない
------------------------------------------------------

#Wham #ワム #LastChristmas #ラストクリスマス #クリスマス #クリスマスソング
#日本語歌詞 #和訳歌詞

snippet.title: Avengers: Doomsday - “Thor odinson Will Return” Trailer | Chris Hemsworth (Concept Version)
snippet.description:
— Attention Viewers ⚠️
— This is a Fan-Made Concept Trailer for:
— Avengers: Doomsday - Thor odinson Will Return

— This video is a fan-made concept trailer, created solely for artistic and entertainment purposes.The goal behind this trailer is to showcase my creativity and storytelling skills through a concept trailer based on a unique and original idea. By combining various effects, sound design, and AI technologies, I’ve crafted a cinematic experience that reimagines familiar worlds in bold and imaginative ways. This trailer is not official and is intended to entertain, inspire, and engage with the YouTube community. Thank you for your support — now let’s dive into a world shaped by creativity and craft. 🎬✨

— In this concept trailer for Avengers: Doomsday, the story reframes the coming conflict through the weight of legacy and responsibility rather than spectacle, centering on a world where familiar heroes are no longer driven by glory but by what they stand to lose. As the multiversal order begins to fracture under an unseen but deliberate hand, the Avengers are forced to confront a threat that challenges not only their strength, but their purpose. Thor’s journey anchors the narrative, revealing a god who has fought for realms and crowns now facing a far more human fear: the need to protect a future embodied in a single child. Doctor Doom emerges not as a force of chaos, but as a calculated architect convinced the multiverse itself must be corrected, placing him on a collision course with heroes who now fight not as warriors, but as guardians. The trailer positions Doomsday as a reckoning, where duty, parenthood, and sacrifice redefine what it truly means to be an Avenger when the fate of existence demands more than victory—it demands return.

snippet.title: AVENGERS DOOMSDAY TEASER Is PURE Desperation… MARVEL Is Out of Ideas.
snippet.description:
Marvel just dropped the AVENGERS DOOMSDAY TEASER, and somehow the biggest takeaway isn’t excitement — it’s desperation.
After writing Steve Rogers out nearly seven years ago, Marvel is suddenly dragging legacy characters back onto the screen in what feels like a last-ditch effort to remind audiences why they used to care. Instead of building new heroes, meaningful arcs, or a coherent future, the MCU seems more interested in recycling the past and hoping nostalgia does the heavy lifting.
In this video, I break down why the Avengers Doomsday teaser feels less like a bold new chapter and more like a panic move from a studio that’s run out of ideas — and why bringing back old characters won’t magically fix Marvel’s deeper storytelling problems.
For more SnarkyJay...

snippet.description:
#netflix #strangerthings5 #strangerthings 

Watch the 'FAN (CONCEPT) Trailer Concept' For Stranger Things - Season 5 (2025) (More Info About This Video Down Below!)
 
 Credits:
     Music: Night Country by Soundridemusic
     Link to Video: https://youtu.be/a-JtvyxlRBQ?si=i7Tezrn-c_oYeavQ

▶️ Watch More Concept Trailers:

Pirates of the Caribbean 6 Trailer - https://youtu.be/uncc9uN0bbI👈

Get ready for the epic conclusion of Netflix's beloved sci-fi horror series with the Stranger Things Season 5 trailer. Set to premiere in November 2025, this final season promises to deliver a thrilling culmination to the Hawkins saga. After delays caused by industry strikes, production wrapped in December 2024, and post-production is ahead of schedule . The Duffer Brothers have crafted an ambitious season described as "eight blockbuster movies," focusing on emotional depth and high-stakes action .

The narrative centers on the Hawkins crew's ultimate battle against Vecna, delving deeper into the mysteries of the Upside Down. Expect a return to the series' roots with a blend of early dynamics and significant character development, particularly highlighting Will's coming-of-age journey . The season will also explore the eerie, time-frozen nature of the Upside Down, potentially incorporating a time jump to align with the aging cast .

The main cast returns, including Millie Bobby Brown, Finn Wolfhard, David Harbour, Winona Ryder, Gaten Matarazzo, Caleb McLaughlin, Noah Schnapp, Sadie Sink, Natalia Dyer, Charlie Heaton, Joe Keery, Maya Hawke, Priah Ferguson, Brett Gelman, Cara Buono, and Jamie Campbell Bower . New additions like Linda Hamilton and Amybeth McNulty join the ensemble, adding fresh dynamics to the story. The eight confirmed episode titles, including "The Crawl," "The Vanishing of…," and "The Rightside Up," hint at a season filled with intrigue and adventure . Don't miss this climactic and nostalgic conclusion to the iconic series.

These mashups often depict a movie that doesn’t exist or shift the genre of an existing film. As derivative works defined under the United States Copyright Act 17 U.S.C. § 101, they may be protected from copyright claims under the fair use doctrine.

Trailer mashups are not just a form of user-generated digital creativity but also a unique way to build excitement for upcoming releases, complementing official movie trailers. While traditional trailers tease the plot and generate hype, fan-made mashups let the audience put their own cinematic twist on existing footage. This creative freedom can spotlight a particular actor, emphasize a specific storyline, or even transform the film’s genre entirely.
